<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinduism_by_country" title="Hinduism by country">Full list</a></td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;"><div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini"><ul><li class="nv-view"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Hinduism_by_country" title="Template:Hinduism by country"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-talk"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template_talk:Hinduism_by_country" title="Template talk:Hinduism by country"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Hinduism_by_country&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>Hinduism is a major religion in India. Hinduism was followed by around 79.8% of the country's population of 1.21&#160;billion (2011 census) (960&#160;million adherents).<sup id="cite_ref-692" class="reference"><a href="Hinduism#cite_note-692">&#91;web 23&#93;</a></sup> Other <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinduism_by_country" title="Hinduism by country">significant populations</a> are found in Nepal (23&#160;million), Bangladesh (15&#160;million) and the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinduism_in_Indonesia" title="Hinduism in Indonesia">Indonesian</a> island of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bali" title="Bali">Bali</a> (3.9&#160;million).<sup id="cite_ref-bps_693-0" class="reference"><a href="Hinduism#cite_note-bps-693">&#91;616&#93;</a></sup> The majority of the Vietnamese <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cham_people" class="mw-redirect" title="Cham people">Cham people</a> also follow Hinduism, with the largest proportion in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ninh_Thu%E1%BA%ADn_Province" title="Ninh Thuận Province">Ninh Thuận Province</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-694" class="reference"><a href="Hinduism#cite_note-694">&#91;617&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Countries with the greatest proportion of Hindus:
</p>
