<li id="cite_note-wendydoniger-304"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="Hinduism#cite_ref-wendydoniger_304-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Hinduism#cite_ref-wendydoniger_304-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Hinduism#CITEREFDoniger1990">Doniger 1990</a>, pp.&#160;2–3: "The Upanishads supply the <b>basis of later Hindu philosophy</b>; they alone of the Vedic corpus are widely known and quoted by most well-educated Hindus, and their central ideas have also become a part of the spiritual arsenal of rank-and-file Hindus."</span>
