<li id="cite_note-jamisonwitzel-549"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="Hinduism#cite_ref-jamisonwitzel_549-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Hinduism#cite_ref-jamisonwitzel_549-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFJamisonWitzel1992" class="citation web">Jamison, Stephanie; Witzel, Michael (1992). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.people.fas.harvard.edu/~witzel/vedica.pdf">"Vedic Hinduism"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. Harvard University. pp.&#160;1–5, 47–52, 74–77<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">4 August</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Vedic+Hinduism&amp;rft.pages=1-5%2C+47-52%2C+74-77&amp;rft.pub=Harvard+University&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.aulast=Jamison&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephanie&amp;rft.au=Witzel%2C+Michael&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.people.fas.harvard.edu%2F~witzel%2Fvedica.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHinduism" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
