<li id="cite_note-629"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Hinduism#cite_ref-629">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFIsaeva1993" class="citation book">Isaeva, Natalia (1993). <span class="cs1-lock-limited" title="Free access subject to limited trial, subscription normally required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/shankaraindianph00isay"><i>Shankara and Indian Philosophy</i></a></span>. State University of New York Press. pp.&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/shankaraindianph00isay/page/n88">79</a>–80. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-7914-1281-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-7914-1281-7"><bdi>978-0-7914-1281-7</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Shankara+and+Indian+Philosophy&amp;rft.pages=79-80&amp;rft.pub=State+University+of+New+York+Press&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7914-1281-7&amp;rft.aulast=Isaeva&amp;rft.aufirst=Natalia&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fshankaraindianph00isay&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHinduism" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>;<br /><cite id="CITEREFIsaeva1995" class="citation book">Isaeva, Natalia (1995). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=GR1h-_mBT_cC"><i>From Early Vedanta to Kashmir Shaivism: Gaudapada, Bhartrhari, and Abhinavagupta</i></a>. State University of New York Press. pp.&#160;137, 163, 171–178. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-4384-0761-6" title="Special:Book